data.text: Mississippi only reports nearly 50 percent fully vaccinated persons. Of those only 37 percent of 12-15 year Olds and 9 percent of 5-11 year Olds. Of the 11, 500 deaths, there have been not 1 death from the vaccine. We must encourage our friends and family to get vaccinated.

Just Asking: Mississippi ranks #1 in deaths per 100K in the last 2 weeks AND #1 in the nation in overall deaths from COVID AND last in the nation in vaccination rates for 5-11 year olds. More US deaths per day than on 9/11 several times this week. Why is this ok?

Mississippi, often a laggard, is No. 1 in America in Covid deaths: 382 per 100k. If Miss. were country, it would rank ninth in world in deaths, slightly better than Moldova. At 50% vaccination rate, it’s at bottom of barrel. Source: NYTimes Covid Tracker. #Mississippi #COVID19
I live in a state with the highest vaccination rate west of the Mississippi. #Washington
